org.jcvi.jillion.sam

Class AbstractSamVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.sam.AbstractSamVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SamVisitor

    public abstract class AbstractSamVisitor
extends Object
implements SamVisitor
    AbstractSamVisitor is an implementation of SamVisitor that implements all the methods of SamVisitor as empty methods. Users may subclass AbstractSamVisitor and override the methods they want to implement.
    Author:
    dkatzel

        public void visitRecord(SamVisitor.SamVisitorCallback callback,
                        SamRecord record,
                        VirtualFileOffset start,
                        VirtualFileOffset end)
        Visit the next SamRecord in the file. If there is valid VirtualFileOffset information available (for example, this is a BAM file, and not a SAM file), then the start and end parameters will be set to something non-null.
        Specified by:
        visitRecord in interface SamVisitor
        Parameters:
        callback - a SamVisitor.SamVisitorCallback that can be used to communicate with the parser object; will be null if the data being visited is not a BAM encoded file.
        record - the SamRecord to visit; ; will be null if the data being visited is not a BAM encoded file.

      • visitHeader

        public void visitHeader(SamVisitor.SamVisitorCallback callback,
                        SamHeader header)
        Description copied from interface: SamVisitor
        Visit the SamHeader of this SAM or BAM file. The SamHeader should contain all the information described in the header section of the SAM or BAM file and also include reference sequence names, program ids etc that are referenced later in the SAM or BAM file.
        Specified by:
        visitHeader in interface SamVisitor
        Parameters:
        callback - a SamVisitor.SamVisitorCallback that can be used to communicate with the parser object; will never be null.
        header - the complete SamHeader for this file; will not be null.
